<HEADLINE> S. Africa Ready for Congo's Peacekeeping Mission </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 28 (Xinhua) -- South African National
Defence Force (SANDF) is ready for a peacekeeping mission to the
war-torn Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC), President Thabo
Mbeki reiterated on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"The army is preparing so that it becomes possible to move
quickly to carry out the peacekeeping mission," Mbeki told South
African Press Association after touring some SANDF units in
Pretoria.
</P>
<P>
Mbeki, also commander-in-chief of the SANDF, inspected the
joint operations division, the military health service, the head
offices of the air force and the engineering unit.
</P>
<P>
He said he was impressed by the work of the SANDF, adding that
much has been done to transform the force.
</P>
<P>
"I was also pleased to see that the engineers are very ready to
continue their work with regard to dealing with disasters such as
the floods that occurred around the country," Mbeki said. 
</P>
